@startuml RevenueAndFeeModule Fee Routing
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #555555
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #444444
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #444444
skinparam sequenceBoxBorderColor #666666
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

title RevenueAndFeeModule - Fee Routing And Revenue Dispatch
autonumber

actor "SubscriptionMgmtModule" as sm
participant "BenefitModule\n(ALP / benefit joins)" as benefit
participant "SFVault" as sf

box "Revenue / Fee Distribution" #E8F5E9
  participant "RevenueAndFeeModule" as raf #C8E6C9
  collections "TLD Fund Buckets\n(in-module balances)" as fund #FFF3E0
end box

participant "ReferralRewardsModule" as rr #C8E6C9
participant "RevShareModule" as rsm #C8E6C9
participant "USDC / ContributionToken" as usdc #EEEEEE

note over raf
Responsibilities in v1:
- classify incoming fee-side cash by command
- forward referral reserve to ReferralRewardsModule
- forward wakala share to RevShareModule
- retain the TLD Fund portion in per-command buckets

Not handled here:
- referral math or parent queueing
- rsNFT / Takadao split math
- crypto-card settlement
end note

== Flow 1: Association Fee ==

sm -> rr ++ : calculateReferralRewards(...)
rr --> sm : feeBaseAmount,\ndiscount,\nreferralReserveAmount
deactivate rr

sm -> raf ++ : dispatchFee(\nCMD_ASSOCIATION_FEE,\nfeeBaseAmount + referralReserveAmount,\nabi.encode(referralReserveAmount)\n)
raf -> raf : validate caller\nvalidate command\nvalidate module state
raf -> usdc : transferFrom(sm, raf, totalAmount)

alt referralReserveAmount > 0
  raf -> usdc : transfer(rr, referralReserveAmount)
end

raf -> raf : wakalaShare = feeBaseAmount * 20 / 100\nfundCredit = feeBaseAmount - wakalaShare

alt wakalaShare > 0
  raf -> usdc : approve(rsm, wakalaShare)
  raf -> rsm ++ : notifyNewRevenue(wakalaShare)
  rsm --> raf : ok
  deactivate rsm
end

raf -> fund : bucket[CMD_ASSOCIATION_FEE] += fundCredit
raf --> sm : FeeDispatchResult(\nfundCredit,\nwakalaShare,\nreferralReserveAmount\n)
deactivate raf

note right of sm
SubscriptionMgmtModule still owns:
- collecting member or coupon funds
- discount handling
- parent reward timing
- member accounting
end note

== Flow 2: ALP / Benefit Fee ==

alt Initial benefit join
  benefit -> rr ++ : calculateReferralRewards(...)
  rr --> benefit : feeBaseAmount,\ndiscount,\nreferralReserveAmount
  deactivate rr

  benefit -> raf ++ : dispatchFee(\nCMD_ALP_FEE,\nfeeBaseAmount + referralReserveAmount,\nabi.encode(referralReserveAmount)\n)
  raf -> raf : same routing logic as association fee
  raf -> usdc : transferFrom(benefit, raf, totalAmount)
  alt referralReserveAmount > 0
    raf -> usdc : transfer(rr, referralReserveAmount)
  end
  raf -> usdc : approve(rsm, wakalaShare)
  raf -> rsm ++ : notifyNewRevenue(wakalaShare)
  rsm --> raf : ok
  deactivate rsm
  raf -> fund : bucket[CMD_ALP_FEE] += fundCredit
  raf --> benefit : FeeDispatchResult(...)
  deactivate raf
else Recurring benefit payment
  sm -> raf ++ : dispatchFee(\nCMD_ALP_FEE,\nfeeAmount,\nbytes(\"\")\n)
  raf -> raf : referralReserveAmount = 0
  raf -> usdc : transferFrom(sm, raf, feeAmount)
  raf -> usdc : approve(rsm, wakalaShare)
  raf -> rsm ++ : notifyNewRevenue(wakalaShare)
  rsm --> raf : ok
  deactivate rsm
  raf -> fund : bucket[CMD_ALP_FEE] += fundCredit
  raf --> sm : FeeDispatchResult(...)
  deactivate raf
end

== Flow 3: SaveFunds / Investment Fee ==

sf -> raf ++ : dispatchFee(\nCMD_SF_MANAGEMENT_FEE |\nCMD_SF_PERFORMANCE_FEE |\nCMD_INVESTMENT_FEE,\nfeeAmount,\nbytes(\"\")\n)
raf -> raf : validate caller == SFVault\nvalidate contribution token only\nreferralReserveAmount = 0
raf -> usdc : transferFrom(sf, raf, feeAmount)
raf -> raf : wakalaShare = feeAmount * 20 / 100\nfundCredit = feeAmount - wakalaShare
raf -> usdc : approve(rsm, wakalaShare)
raf -> rsm ++ : notifyNewRevenue(wakalaShare)
rsm --> raf : ok
deactivate rsm
raf -> fund : bucket[command] += fundCredit
raf --> sf : FeeDispatchResult(\nfundCredit,\nwakalaShare,\n0\n)
deactivate raf

== Flow 4: Compatibility Revenue Deposit ==

note over raf
Temporary compatibility path for older flows such as
SubscriptionModule.transferSubscriptionToReserve(...).
This is not fee routing.
It just buckets already-classified revenue in the TLD Fund.
end note

sm -> raf ++ : depositRevenue(amount, RevenueType)
raf -> raf : map RevenueType to a compatibility bucket
raf -> usdc : transferFrom(sm, raf, amount)
raf -> fund : compatibilityBucket[RevenueType] += amount
raf --> sm : ok
deactivate raf

== Flow 5: Reserved Card Commands ==

note over raf
Reserved in v1:
- CMD_CARD_SUBSCRIPTION_FEE
- CMD_CARD_USAGE_FEE

Both revert UnsupportedRoute()
until the card-provider and card-holder sinks exist.
end note

@enduml
